title: Rate of homicide in Canada and the United States 2000 to 2018
summary: Overall United States is gradually decreasing, Canada is roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The order of lines according to average values of Rate of himicide per 100 thousand residents, in descending order is: 1. United States, and lastly, 2. Canada.
The minimum Rate of himicide per 100 thousand residents about 1.56, occured at 2012 by Canada.
The greatest difference of Rate of himicide per 100 thousand residents between Canada and United States occurs at Year 2007 and the smallest difference occurs at 2011.
